summary: Harry waking up the day after the wedding and remembering that you are finally his.  My heart melts hahaha
question: Harry waking up the day after the wedding and remembering that you are finally his.  My heart melts hahaha
answer:
“stop fussing.”

harry’s gonna grumble once he feels you moving yet again on his grasp, and his eyes are still closed shut with already the half of his body on top of yours at this point now.

“s’noon.”

you say even though you haven’t seen the actual time yet, and you could bet that it is with how much light is peeking from behind the curtains and the information doesn’t faze him one bit.

the room’s a bit of a mess. things here and there. lingerie on the side. wedding dress and his wedding suit on an armchair.

“don’t care. you’re m’wife now.”

he hears a chuckle and he could practically tell you’re thinking on how that information’s relevant to what you just said and what you’re implying.

harry’s still in cloud nine, even if he’s exhausted yet well-rested at the same time and how his body aches and thrives, his hair a mess and it’s being put back with your head as you notice it, and he doesn’t like his hair bothering his face.

harry smiles, and only takes that as invitation to turn you around and literally put you on top of him, and he’s still sleepy and soft and only smiles at the little ‘oof!’ you’ve let out.

“gonna love on you any time i want now.”

summary: Harry Styles Tour Tally: Nearly 1 Million Tickets Sold, $1.2 Million in Charity Donations (EXCLUSIVE)
title: Harry Styles Tour Tally: Nearly 1 Million Tickets Sold, $1.2 Million in Charity Donations (EXCLUSIVE)
body:
Initial numbers from the tour — which wrapped last weekend with two dates at the Forum in Inglewood, Calif. — evidence an impressive run. (All were provided to Variety by Full Stop Management and Live Nation.)
*89 sold-out shows
*Just under 1 million tickets sold
*First arena tour to sell out through Ticketmaster’s new Verified Fan program, with the first leg selling out in 29 seconds
*The second of the two final shows at the Forum in Inglewood, Calif., tallied more than 17,000 paid tickets and beat the record for most paid tickets for a single show since the venue reopened in 2014
*Merchandise records set in over 50 venues in North and South America, Australia and Europe
The tour’s charitable impact, for which Styles partnered with the nonprofit Reverb:

*Raised $1.2 million in charity donations (ticket contributions, Live Nation contributions and matching payments, local matches and the GLSEN PRIDE campaign) across 62 charities around the world (here for a complete list https://hstyles.co.uk/tpwk)
*Registered hundreds of new voters via Headcount
*Made a major effort for water conservation that:
-saved the equivalent of 10,000 single-use water bottles by fans and 3,200 by the band and crew
-recycled more than 6,500 gallons of water from buses, offices, dressing rooms and other backstage areas
-led to more than 5,000 direct connections between fans and the local charities

Variety
